cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.SI

This paper deals with the problem of mitigating the Forwarding Information Base (FIB) overflow problem, which is a common issue in network routing. The paper proposes a new algorithm for FIB aggregation that is faster and has a lower memory footprint than existing solutions. This work involves network infrastructure and algorithms for handling large amounts of data, which suggests that it could be categorized under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Additionally, the paper discusses the security implications of FIB overflow and proposes solutions, which could place it under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The algorithmic nature of the proposed solution suggests that it could also be categorized under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the algorithm using realistic routing tables, which could place it under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
